    {
      "text": "\n\n**APP Channel Momentum:**\n- **172,625 total app transactions** in Q4 (27.8% of total transaction volume)\n- **$21.78 average order value**\u2014essentially matching in-store ($21.74) and exceeding third-party delivery\n- **$3.76M in app revenue** with 96.6% margin retention (vs 52-59% on third-party delivery)\n- APP performed on par with owned channels (Web, Kiosk, In-Store) while maintaining full margin control\n\n## Strategic Implications\n\n**The 1-3-5 promotion successfully acquired high-quality guests at scale.** The 89.3% retention rate is best-in-class for promotional acquisition and signals that discounted first visits are converting to habitual app usage. The economics are compelling: while first visit AOV was lower due to discount mechanics ($19.17), second visit normalized to near-parity ($19.62), and the app maintains 96.6% margin vs 52-59% on delivery platforms.\n\n**Recommended Action:** Scale the APP135 promotion structure to new markets and reactivation campaigns. The 4.1-point retention lift and strong repeat visit economics justify continued investment in app-first acquisition strategies.\n",
